---
source: crates/ridge-lexer/tests/snapshots.rs
expression: render(URL_SHORTENER)
---
0..382 DOC_COMMENT "An in-memory URL shortener.  A single actor, Store, owns the code→URL mapping.\nAn HTTP server translates POST /shorten and GET /:code into actor messages.\nShort codes are 6-character base-62 strings generated with std.random.\nThe actor's internal `random` capability is encapsulated; HTTP handler callers\nonly require `time` for the implicit ask timeout (Model B, §6.4)."
